The paper addresses a machine learning problem of feature acquisition with a focus on reducing misclassification cost. This problem is commonly studied in the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a framework that utilizes probabilistic inference and conditional independence properties, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of computational engineering (cs.CE), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
